From a4ca8cf51453ecfadfedfe486c5577875137a269 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yasuhiro Niji <niji@yniji.net>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 08:00:07 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] [vector_graphics_compiler] Support SVG vertical writing modes
 (CJK tategaki)

flutter_svg silently renders vertical (writing-mode) text horizontally:
the parser tracks writing-mode through the attribute cascade
(_heritableProps) but the text path never reads it. Flutter's paragraph
builder has no vertical layout, so this change decomposes vertical text
at compile time in the resolver into per-cell horizontal text draws,
using only existing IR primitives (no codec/runtime changes):

- upright glyphs stacked along the block axis
- rotational vertical forms (brackets, dashes, long sound mark) rotated
  90 degrees; ideographic full stop/comma moved to the cell's top-right
  corner (font-independent: no reliance on U+FE10..FE4F glyph coverage)
- tate-chu-yoko: 1-2 char ASCII alphanumeric runs stay upright
- tspan attribute cascade and absolute positioning (new column)
  supported; dx/dy falls back to horizontal rendering

Adds 10 tests; all 339 package tests pass.
