+## 1.3.0
+
+* Adds support for SVG vertical writing modes (`writing-mode: vertical-rl` /
+  `vertical-lr` / `tb` / `tb-rl`), used primarily by CJK text. Vertical text
+  is decomposed at compile time into per-cell horizontal text draws: upright
+  glyphs are stacked along the block axis, characters whose vertical form is
+  a rotation (brackets, dashes, the long sound mark) are rotated 90°,
+  ideographic full stops/commas move to the top-right corner of their cell,
+  and runs of one or two ASCII alphanumerics stay upright (tate-chū-yoko).
+  `tspan` attribute cascading and absolute positioning (new column) are
+  supported; `dx`/`dy` fall back to the previous horizontal behavior.
+
 ## 1.2.6
 
 * Fixes `linux-arm64` host support by selecting the Flutter engine
